content.detailedDescription: I was outside getting the fire pit ready for a bonfire when i noticed what seemed to be a blinking red orb slowly passing overhead.  at first, i tried to identify it as a helicopter due to the fact that i previously had seen 3 of them fly overhead a few hours earlier.  i watched the object continue on a northwest direction and eventually lost it over the tops of trees.  immediately after i lost sight of the object i walked into the garage to grab something and when i came out i noticed what seemed to be a very bright star in the northwest sky.  then, the bright white light is gone and the red object/orb begins heading in a southeast direction.  as i'm watching it heading to the southeast the object stops again and remains in the same place for maybe 10 to 15 minutes.  the object then headed in a southwest direction and i eventually lost it.  i can tell you this...  this object was not a helicopter.  there was no sound, a change of color, and it was moving in a way that a conventional aircraft could not.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Life changing.

content.detailedDescription:
i was 18yrs old living in highland ca on central av and  had arrived home at about 10:30 pm on a friday night and had started to unlock my front door when i heard a pulsating, whirring sound i had never heard before or since. i turned to look in the direction of the sound and saw 4 bright flood type lights about 2 to 3 foot in diameter pointing straight down. the night was crystal clear but i couldn't see anything but the lights. the craft was moving at about 10mph from west to east over a mobile home park on east 9th st (still there) about 250ft away. at first i thought someone had invented a new flying power plant that was making such an odd sound. as it moved east a tree blocked my view so i moved to regain line of sight and observed it cross central av about 75ft north of e9th st over an unpopulated area (at the time), the whirring sound then increased in frequency to a level above my hearing range in about 2sec. the lights then began to ascend nne, accelerating from about 10mph to more than supersonic speed in 1 second, without any sonic boom, and blended into the stars, then disappearing completely as it moved away. 
 i had been in the civil air patrol for several years and had training in flight physics so i knew this was beyond any public knowledge of flight.
 i believe i witnessed an extra terrestrial craft on a close up reconnaissance of human life.
content.summary: 4 bright flood lights in a rectangle pattern just above the tree tops

content.detailedDescription: I was on my way to the gym, traveling east on goodman road in olive branch, mississippi on may 6, 2014 around 9:30 a.M.  i noticed that there was one single, small cloud in the sky that day directly in line with my car.  i watched it and noticed that it wasn't round and fluffy, but angular.  as i watched, it seemed to swirl and my first thought was that it was a whirlwind, but then i saw just the left side end and botton edge of an oval shape within the cloud. it was a light blue color.  i kept watching and within about 3 seconds everything just dissipated.  i thought it was odd that the cloud wasn't blown by the wind but just disappeared.  i thought maybe it was smoke, but there were no other planes nearby.  i also wondered why it was the only cloud in an otherwise cloudless day.  i wondered how it could have disappeared so quickly.  i continued to the gym and worked out.  when i got home i told my husband about it and then documented it.
content.summary: While driving i noticed a single, small,  angular cloud in the sky that seemed to swirl.  i saw the outside edge of a light blue oval shaped object.  it all disappeared within about 3 seconds.

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i placed a blanket on the beach around 9:00 pm to watch the stars since there wasn't a cloud in the sky.  after about 15 minutes of big dipper locating, i mentioned to wife that it looked like there was a bond fire way down the beach west of us.  as we both looked at it, it appeared to be moving and started coming towards us.  we had our yorkie with us and were letting her run around without a leash so we decided we better put the leash on her because we thought it maybe the coastal police (orange headlight) on patrol.  as it continued towards us, it looked like it was hovering just above the surf, then when it got within a football field it ascended like a chinese lantern and appeared to burn out as it ascended, then we could barely see a skeleton of it as if it were a large ember.

we rationalized that it was a chinese sky lantern but couldn't figure how it could hover just off the groung up the beach towards us for a long distance, then ascend?

after about 30 minutes, we experienced the first event of the orange orbs that were about 500 feet over the water and about a mile off the coast.  they had the color of a jack o lantern and the approximate size of a pea held at arms link.

at first only one orb appeared (like someone turned on a light) and hovered for a few seconds, then went out.  couple seconds later, it came on again but about a quarter of a mile left of the area where we saw first one.  then 3 came on all at once together and hovered for about 5 seconds.  after these went out, we noticed what looked like tiny white stars flashing intermittently in a tight group.  we watched the flickering stars fade away and didn't see anything for another 10 minutes.  this time, we saw the grouped white flickering first and said, "here they come again"...And sure enough we saw the same orange orbs comenon again and hover for a few seconds multiple times.

this happened numerous times over the course of about an hour. the most we saw at one time was 5.

we finally decided to go get the cell phone and call 911 to report it about 10:45 pm.  while i was on the phone with the dispatcher, one more appeared and i said, "look honey, there's another one"!

we sat there for another 45 minutes waiting for the police and never saw another thing, not even the police.
content.summary: Observed 4-5 orange orbs over ocean multiple times for a period of 1-1/2 hours.  we saw fast blinking white tiny lights then the orbs would light up and hover then go off again.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving northbound on cicero ave. looked up to the sky . i first thought the object was an airplane ,flying south[toward me] with the sun reflecting off of it there for looking unusual. since it looked interesting i continued keeping an eye on it while driving. the object/light appeared staionary from a great distance away as i watched it started to give off an intense glowing white light [it was white to begin with] at this point i thought i was seeing something very unusual and it had my full attention after it started glowing [i do not think this was sun reflection ] it just completly vanished  no contrail no evidence it was ever there to begin with. this is important- the whole time i watched this there was an airplane to the right of the light .Significantly  lower than the light [its possible the plane was decending as this was around midway airport]the light was approximately 3-4 times the size of the plane the features of the plane were well defined and easily distinguished as a plane. there were no clouds in the sky.My feeling was that i saw something very unusual and i contacted mufon hoping somebody else had reported something similar, thus giving my account some credibility. i lost sight of the object/light when it disappeared.
content.summary: Strange glowig white light above airplane

content.detailedDescription: I was on vacation in myrtle beach, sc laying on the bed watching a movie when i noticed a bright orange light outside my window over the ocean. i was staying on the beach so my view was nothing but the ocean. i looked at the light for a few seconds and it turned into 3 bright orange/red lights. i immediately ran outside on the balcony to watch it more. it quickly disappeared but then more lights appeared shortly after in a triangular pattern. the lights would shift into several lights and then back into 1 before vanishing. this happened for about an hour. at first i was just looking straight out over the ocean looking for the orange/red lights but for some reason i looked up into the sky right above me and i saw a huge stealth like craft. it was a fluke that i actually even saw it cause it was almost invisible but i could make out the shape and lights on the bottom of the craft. at first it moved slowly and then in a matter of seconds it disappeared. it was shaped like a long boomerang with tons of lights on the bottom of it. i couldn't believe how close it was! after that the lights only appeared one more time and i caught video of it that time. i stayed up for hours though just watching the sky and noticed about 3 hours later a blue light in the sky that after a few seconds turned into 2 orange/red lights and just hovered over the water before disappearing.
content.summary: Several orange lights over the ocean and then a stealth like craft flying above our heads

content.detailedDescription:
Justwas in back yard watching for meteors, at about 3:45 am. was watching towards northeast sky. we had seen 3 meteors and a few satellites. we had seen afew high flying jets also. then about 4:15am i spotted a bright light moving straight overhead towsrds the northeast. at fist i thought it was another satellite, but 
realized it 
wasnt because 
it was much 
brighter, like a 




star and never 
changed 

brightness. it 
was not 
making any 
sound and no 
trails left 
behind. there




were no 
flashing lights, 
like we saw on the airplanes. it moved across the sky following a straight path from directly above me when i first noticed it, to the northeast horizon ahead of me. although it was going in a straight path, it was zigzagging from side to side as it moved along. it kept going, not changing brightness, until it finally disappeared over the horizon.

observed on all the planes we saw.
content.summary: Saw bright light moving northeast and zig zagging

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were headed home from nashville and were a few miles north of murfreesboro when i noticed a strange light in the sky to the south-west. i believed it was a plane at first, then a helicopter due to it never seeming to move. i assumed i was following it by coincidence. as we started coming closer to it, my wife suggested it was a tower that had a malfunctioning light. then it slowly crossed the interstate, heading north-east and then sped away, about 5 times faster than it had previously been hovering. the object itself, as it finally flew overhead, i could tell was very flat, but upright, and diamond-shaped. it glowed white and pulsates at a rather even rate. at random times a blue light flashed from its bottom area, but not in any regular pattern. i was excited by seeing it and it raised many questions for me. we lost sight of it due to driving down i-24 and the fact it randomly sped away at an angle behind us.
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Flat pulsating diamond shape slowly hovering across interstate than changed direction and sped away.

content.detailedDescription: In the late afternoon, around 5:30 pm, my wife, son and i were out in the backyard. the weather was fair and clear. approx. 75 degrees with no wind. unlimited visibility. as we stood together between some trees i noticed a "bird" almost directly overhead. it appeared from overhead a 30" tree canopy from the e. it moved in various sharp angles to a hover, and then back and forth between sharp angular turns to hover over and over for about 15 seconds. we all watched it. after approx. 15 seconds the "bird" moved off back to the e direction over the tree top it appeared from. the "bird" resembled the size of a large raven. it was black. it had a segmented body. the body was that of a long tappered elipse with a round head with a long pointed "beak". the "wings" resembled that of a dragonfly and it moved about like a hummingbird. we discussed what it might have been and i said a hummingbird, because i have seen them before and they darted about like that but knew that they are quite small at close range and this was no bird because of it's size, structure, and movement. i am a skilled observer. as soon as it moved away back to the e over the tree top <and dissapeared>, immediately at the exact same elevation and area of the sky appeared from over the tree top an off white colored object from the e. it looked round at first. it seemed to be at a very high altitude and it moved at constant speed and direction like that of a high altitude commercial jet. there were about 30 degrees of overhead visibility inbetween the trees. i called it out and my son eventualy picked it up just before it disappeared over the treeline to the west. the elipse was slightly egg shaped, the point was at the front. the edges were clealy defined. there were no lights on it or reflections. i checked the weather conditons the next day with the nws and the winds were light about 5 mph from the w. my estimation was that it was as large as a commercial jet at altitude.
content.summary: Flying object resembling a bird, that was obviously not, observed overhead making right angle turns and hovering, proceeded in the same view point by an off white colored  elipse that was egg shaped at an apparent high altitude.

content.detailedDescription:
Traveling from l.A. to sacramento ca, five witnesses in the truck total. object first appeared due east while traveling north from bakersfield, but before fresno. three occupants of the car were panicking so we could not stop to watch, but the object seemed to stay with us. the highway was busy, moving a little slow that night, though traffic never fully stopped. nobody else seemed to pull over, and i don't believe the ufo was to blame for the traffic.

i was not the first person to spot the ufo. a passenger commented that there was a suspicious plane in the sky, and i looked around until i spotted it to the east from the passenger side, telling them after a few moments that the maneuvers it had been doing as i had watched it were not indicative of an airplane, and that it was a ufo.

triangle was a black triangular shape in the sky, with three white lights on the bottom of the craft. as it flew over the highway, it blocked starlight, and it spun horizontally clockwise at roughly 1 rotation per 2 seconds, roughly.

continued to spin as it crossed back over the highway and began to descend towards the orchard next to us, moving with us perpendicular to the highway. object would then rise and repeat the same maneuver, dipping towards the highway. came visibly close to a farmhouse in one orchard, perceived to be less than 200 feet away at one point when crossing over us, and the farmhouse. from the closest observation i had, the ufo was roughly 150 feet in diameter.


on some occasions it made sharp right turns, or fully reverse movement with only slight deceleration. it would maintain altitude when doing these maneuvers.

motions appeared to be deliberate or for a test flight, as the object was moving fluidly and seemed to be bringing it low across the fields, and then ascending, repeating the action (descending/ascending while rotating) for roughly 20-25 minutes until it slowly ascended and then began to accelerate west-northwest. 

acceleration was not instantaneous, though it eventually reached incredible speeds heading away from us (growing smaller rapidly) before growing too small in the sky to see over the course of roughly 30 seconds.

attempted to take photos with a phone, but the images couldn't capture the three lights or shape of the object, which was quite dim (not much brighter than the brightest star in the sky at the time, despite light pollution from nearby cars in moderate traffic.)

other passengers in the car were getting very spooked (teenage girls aged 16-18) and were growing more nervous when talking to one-another about the 'what would happen if(s)' should things progress beyond a sighting, as the object would hover quite close over the highway and i asked about pulling over.

i remained calm and watched the ufo for the entirety of the flight. it was only out of my field of vision a few times during the entire encounter, when it went behind the car to the south-east for a full minute.

the driver was focusing on the traffic, as the night had been particularly hectic with at least two drunk drivers threatening the road. she caught a few glimpses of the object, but was more worried about driving.

we talked about the ufo for a long time after the event that night, as there was still a few hours of driving needed to get home.

i have included a paint sketch of the relative observed size(s) of the object in the sky.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: Large triangle ufo appeared from east, crossed over highway spinning horizontally, blocking starlight. crossed back over highway spinning low above orchard. repeated several times.

content.detailedDescription:
Last night 05/05/14, my girlfriend and i were leaving my apartment and i wanted to show off my nerdom, pointed out mars to her and as we looked i saw what i assumed was a satellite, moving fast from the south to the north. we kept and eye on it, about half way across the sky it flashed a very luminous white light, moved for another 5 seconds and did it again, at which point my girlfriend began to freak out and we walked out of my backyard. this was around 9:30pm est.

the flash was brilliant white, like a camera flash, this "unknown object" appeared to be a satellite and very far away and moving fast went behind some wispy clouds when the first flash occurred, another a few seconds later after is moved from behind the cloud.
content.summary: Nyc brilliant flash of light from star like object.

content.detailedDescription:
my wife and i were coming home from getting dinner at approximately 8:30. we were heading out of whitewater, wi and heading towards jeffferson. about two miles outside of whitewater i noticed something huge in the sky. it had a redish blinking light and also a white blinking light. i pointed it out to my wife and she said it was probably two planes flying really close together. i told her to take a closer look. it was pretty dark at this point but i could see that it was on huge object. she looked closer and realized that too.

my wife, who isn't a believer in ufo's said we should follow it because she was completely at a loss of words for what it was we were looking at. we followed it for about 45 minutes to an hour. occasionally it would have one reddish light and three white lights. it moved slowly sometimes coming close to the ground, not much higher than the treetops. at one point we lost sight of it and as we came over a hill i saw it again, at first i didn't think it was the object. i thought it was maybe a large billboard with lights on it, then i realized we were in the middle of nowhere and there wouldn't be any billboards around. i stopped the vehicle and noticed that it was still moving, but was pretty close to us. we watched it and changed directions and altitude numerous times.

i got out of the vehicle to try to get video of it, but unfortunately all i had was my samsung galaxy s4 to shoot video of it. the video is not very good and for some reason you could only see the reddish light in the video, and not any of the white lights. i got back in the vehicle to follow it some more but by this time it had flown quite far from us and we lost sight of it.

a mile or two later we saw it again and it was much higher in the sky. not too far from it we noticed another light in the sky. this was a white twinkling light. it would twinkle a few times and then there would be no light coming from it for a second or two, then it would twinkle again for a few seconds and then go dark again. we watched this object in the sky for a few moments noticing that it would decend at a rapid speed for short distances. we could still see it in the sky at approximately 9:30 as we were heading back home.

i honestly have no idea what we saw. the first craft we saw was huge, much bigger than any plane i have ever seen. it also moved slow for quite a while at low altitudes. there are a few small airports close by, but there is no way anything this large would be able to land or take off from them. my wife and i are puzzled by what we saw and followed around for almost an hour.
content.summary: Large craft noticed. looked to be approximately 100 yrds long. my wife and i followed it for about 45 minutes before it was out of view.

content.detailedDescription: Standing on back deck, heard helicopter approaching waited and expected to see helicopter go in direction of hospital.  came in fast from sw then noticed small white light leading the helicopter. as the helicopter came in closer it moved off to the northeast following the small light that seemed to be leading the chopper at a fairly high rate of speed in a straight direction.  flight never varied and didn't go in the direction of hospital.  local airport should have picked up the helicopter in the area.  there is on occasion military helicopters in and out of our airport that come out of the springfield reserve.
content.summary: Helicopter chasing small bright light

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were driving back home from a day of shopping at the sommerset mall in troy, mi, when we were driving on 75 n bound at 934 pm, about a mile before the next exit e holly rd. 

we saw a red ball of light that blinked a faw times and moved so fast across the expressway that it couldn't of been a plane or helicopter and it was right above the tree line not high in the sky at all. it happened so fast we both looked at each other and couldn't believe what we saw. 

we are creeped out right now, and we have never been a believer until now, i know it couldnt of been anything normal. this was out of this world. 

i called it in to the mi state police and he sounded like it wasn't the first time he heard this story. i looked it up online and noticed more people are seeing the same thing.
content.summary: A red orb appeared in front of us, flashed and flew so fast out of site. nothing man made that i can think of

content.detailedDescription: Was out in my yard around 8:30 pm on january 26th, 2014 when i saw a large triangular shaped ufo flying in a circular pattern around a general area of what was probably a few miles. when i first saw it, it was in the northeastern area of the sky around atlanta, but it flew around in such a large circular pattern that i'd eventually lose sight of it before it would appear again. i first assumed it was a stealth bomber making a test flight, as georgia is home to many military bases, but that thought disappeared one it broke from its previous flight path and started rapidly descending, ascending, and turning in such a way that i have never seen a human pilot be capable of doing. soon enough it had what appeared to be a fighter jet trailing it around, but this only lasted a few minutes before the jet flew away from the object. the object flew around in its circular pattern for around forty minutes, with the jet trailing it only once it broke from its flight path. it kept flying erratically for another 15-20 minutes before it disappeared back into the general area i originally saw it from. my grandmother also came out to see the object, but only through a window, and she has finally asked me to send a report in to someone we hope may know about this strange occurence. any help is greatly appreciated.
content.summary: Saw a triangular ufo with three lights that blinked, fizzled, and faded at alternating paces. flew in a circular pattern before disappearing in northeast direction.

content.detailedDescription:
Observed horizon to horizon passage of a brighter than normal reddish pink light source. source moved similar to a low earth orbital craft originating in the southwest moving silently north ending at the horizon to the northwest. object lost definition three times puffing out to an aspirin sized cloud back lit. these puffs were rapid in creation and dissipation. object was not a nav beacon as there were no other lights on the craft nor were there any rhythmic attenuations observed. possible the ufo was a piece of space debris burning up in de-orbit.

conditions was clear cool and dry in baton rouge. no clouds were in the vicinity. no sounds we're heard. speed of object made the lack of sound rather curious. my first thought was that the object was the sis, but it was the wrong color. oberevation was made at 8:52pm.
content.summary: Ufo possible satellite burnup

content.detailedDescription:
Sitting in yard observing sunset as we always do and noticed this unusual event. i had a major sighting on 9/11/2001  over bioyn ny  which i never reported. the watch took first place and was trying to get to manhattan to get my kids out. saw a craft clear as could be doed shape with row of windows around ,no sound ,very big, observed many others watching it but left it there as we all had places to go and the adrenalin was pumping due to the attack on wtc. thought about what i saw later when i went to girlfriends as i wasn't allowed back into manhattan that day...And sunk in what i saw...Amazing ... however what we saw tonight was  very bright red and green lights moving at a very high rate of speed , stopped on a dime and headed back in the opposite direction at the same high rate of speed...Wow....
thank you
content.summary: Object flying at least 10 to 20 faster than aircraft flying over newark airport . heading south stopped on dime and shot back north at same rate of speed

content.detailedDescription: Driving down huron river southbound dr. observed orb near huron hills golf course. about 400 meters away. vertically lifted and hovered for 3 sec the ascended into the clouds heading north and the light vanished as well.
content.summary: Orb vertically lifted off stopped and headed north

content.detailedDescription: I was at a music fest in my town. i was admiring the moon and the huge halo around it. i noticed something come up from behind the mountains in the distance. it was the opposite direction of planes usual paths so i kept watching. it had an upward arched curve from the moment it started.. it continued the same upward motion until it was next to and past the moon..Up up up til out of sight. it was round seem to glow or reflect gently. it had a steady fairly slow and even ascension. it appeared to be bluish. it left behind a very distinct 'chem trail' which never faded and never dissipated until after the object was gone. i had many people looking at the moon and when i saw the object first appear from behind the mountain i had everyone there watching it as well.
content.summary: I was at a music show in my town. i was admiring the moon and the huge halo around. i noticed something come up from behind the mountains.

content.detailedDescription: Was taking pictures of the sky outside of my house when i looked at the pictures the object was only in one of the pictures nothing before nothing after don't know what the object could be but it was very strange
content.summary: Took several pics of sky and the object popped in and out of view very quick

content.detailedDescription: We were sitting in the back yard and my husband noticed something moving quickly over our neighbors house.  we ran to the front yard and watched the lights zig zag quickly as it dropped rapidly toward the skyline.  the descent was faster than any object we have ever witnessed falling from the sky.  the lights were solid (not flashing)and were closer together than what would be seen on an airplane, almost right next to each other.  the lights descended from about a 60 degree angle to the tree line in less than 15 seconds.
content.summary: Extremely fast moving red and blue green light, changed directions and then dropped quickly to skyline

content.detailedDescription: It was supposed to be a regular night where my husband and i would go outside to look to the sky with the telescope! i was standing to his left when i suddently looked up and saw this ufo "machine" rectangle brown colour moving slowly, when i called out to my husband to take a look at it and pointed it, it started to go faster until it dissapeard, he just took a glazed at it, i was amazed and felt somewhat scared, we took everything and went inside! this has not been my only episode of seeing ufo's! i have also felt that they call me out of my house to see them, or to know that they're there! have tons of dreams with them coming to get me, really strange since everywhere i go.. i feel they're watching me. have seen them a total of 7 times during my lifetime, am now 25 yrs old. wonder how much more and if i have something they might want from me?!
content.summary: Just appeared out of nowhere.

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were walking back to the trailhead of bell rock trail in the village of oak creek in sedona az. we both saw a sandwich like shape in front of the mouton across the street from us.  it looked like a circle of light red to orange on top then a line more metallic then bright blue below. the blue overpower a bit and the colors blended together. we compared the object to the people we saw hiking atop nearby mountains the people looked like ants so we thought the object must be the size of a car or more.  the mountain is red and we could see the object very well with the mt.  as back ground. the object moved in a perfectly straight line from north to south for about 10 seconds then vanished. from our observation it disappeared at the end of the mountain so perhaps it could have turned the corner. the mountain is very high and we ruled out it being any kind of high tech toy based on the size and perfect straight line and it seemed to completely disappear in our sight.
content.summary: Standing at the entrance to bell rock trail in the voc, my husband and i saw a sandwich like shape with blue red/orange with line in btw moving in straight line then disappear after about 10 seconds of watching.

content.detailedDescription:
I was taking photos of us rise.
when i was taking the photo, i didn't see that green spot at all.
after i got home, i saw the green spot on three photos and different position.
content.summary: I found the ufo after i got home checking photos

content.detailedDescription: Chris m, don g and myself, with myself driving where heading west to madison, mn from white bear lake, mn where i have relatives to go camping for the weekend. left in the evening after we all got off work and had had dinner. all three of us where 19 years old at that time. it is a three hour drive to our destination. we where about 2 and a half hours into drive heading west on mn highway 40 and it was just at dark with nothing but farm land as far as you can see in all directions. i caught sight of something off in the distinct to my right. as i am driving west the object i saw was heading south we where getting closer to each other. i was getting to the spot on the highway where we would meet, so i pulled over and waited for it to come south to us. when we got close to each other we saw it was two aircrafts flying head to tail in a straight line. we all three stayed inside the van looking out the front windshield and watched the two three story apartment building size crafts pass by in front of us. they where going slow maybe three to five miles per hour. they where identical crafts parallelogram shape 40 feet tall 200 feet long and 20 feet wide with three rows of windows on the sides each about 10 feet by 10 feet. the bottom of the craft had what looked like a trap door two panels that would open to one opening size of 15ft x 30 ft. in the center of the crafts bottom side. they where gray metallic in color with the windows all lite up white. we watched them go off to the south out of sight in about a ten minuet time span. they both had two round orange red glowing spots on the rear of the craft, one on top of the other. after they where out of sight we all three where in shock of what we just saw. i sat there on the side of the highway for about five minutes. when i went to pull out and start heading west again i noticed that two other cars had pulled over behind me also. we started west again and about two miles down the highway i saw two more of the same crafts again to my right. they where identical to the two we just watched. this time when i pulled over don and i both got out of the van and stood in the middle of the highway watching them fly right over our heads. i stood there with my chin on the floor in awe of what i was seeing. don g was waving his arms above his head yelling  beam me up. we could hear a deep rumble as they passed us going to the south same as two prior. you could feel the ground vibrating under our feet. they had no wings or any propulsion from the bottom. we thought they must of had some kind of magnetic force to keep them up? remember they are the size of apartment buildings in the air 30ft above our heads barely moving. when we could not see them anymore we released chris m was not out in the road with us. we found him hiding in the back of the van scared out of his mind. that was 34 years ago and i will never forget it. i know that changed my life for ever. sometimes i think that maybe i was under a spell of even abducted because it seemed to be such a long time we watched this event and had some difficulty with time frames between the three of us?
content.summary: Four total ufo's. two at a time all in twenty minute time frame.

content.detailedDescription: It was tuesday morning, i was leaving homedepot and as im walking out the door i just look up. its just something i do now due to the experiences ive encounter in the past. well back to what i was saying i was looking up while i was leaving home depot something really big came down really low above me forming a mushroom shape cloud camouflaging itself under it. im looking around me and there's no one around me, no noise and i started seeing things come out from under it were black disk objects, and one that was just hovering observing everything around me, this object is on the right side of the cloud. and the other to the top left of the cloud. i also noticed a small figure on top of the van in front of me really small green camouflage figure.I quickly jumped in my work van took a pic, caught all three images in one. than took another one when the objects that were hovering were  going back into the cloud, and whatever was on that van in front of me disappears. than within 2 minutes or so the cloud goes out of a mushroom shaped cloud to nothing and the object below disappears.

content.detailedDescription:
I had gone outside to let our dogs out. while out there i caught a glimpse of something moving in the sky. looking up i saw it was what appeared to be normal commercial air traffic. my house sits along the flight path of a few of the airports,lakeland/tampa/orlando, so seeing planes both day and night are a normal occurrence. as the plane flew off in the distance i happened to see what at first appeared to be another plane headed towards me, the strange part was that it was headed 90 degrees from the normal flight paths i see every day. my first thoughts were it was a plane as i saw red and green lights, but also white and blue and yellow.  and i was seeing them head on, like said, as if the plane was headed towards me. 

then it dawned on me, the lights were moving yet the "plane" wasn't. what i was seeing was the lights in random order moving right to left, and changing intensity as they did. they would go from dim to bright or flash bright and then dim, at the same time they were moving right to left. and it was all of the lights that moved. these lights did not follow a sequence as i would have expected. they would flash, i guess is the best description, anywhere in their horizontal movement, sometimes all the way on the right or left, sometimes in the middle, or even in between the line they were on.
i'm very failure with aviation, and this was not normal nav lamps/strobes/landing lamps on an aircraft. the lights were in a horizontal line, not staggered like on an aircraft.And there was a glow of yellow/white light behind all of the lights.

and like said, what ever it was didn't move, it was planted in one spot, not getting closer or further away, nor moving up or down. i started using visible landmarks to confirm it wasn't moving in the sky. while doing so i noted that it was not alone. there was a second one off to the right and above it, and was either smaller or further away.  similar moving lights, yet an unmoving craft. distance/size is hard to tell at night. from my viewpoint the first was around the size of a basketball in diameter, the other more closer to a tennis ball.  neither had a visible shape/structure other then the glow of light behind the row of moving lights.

i watched both for close to a half hour, comparing them to the stars, and other aircraft in the sky. the lights were not anything like any of the other airplanes i saw, nor were they like the light from the stars. and neither moved from it's spot in the sky.  the viewing angle i had eliminated any ground source, nothing on the ground is that high, and even a helicopter or blimp can't just park in one spot in the sky for that long.   and when they left it was like someone just turned off a light switch. they both just blinked off.
no lights, nothing, i searched the sky to see if they had moved but couldn't see anything except the stars in the sky and one obvious aircraft.
i heard no sounds at all from either "craft" while i observed them.

funny while typing this i realized that both my dogs went in the house when this occurred, normally they stay outside with me. also i honestly don't remember hearing any other sounds while viewing these things. no neighborhood noises, and even some of the true aircraft i saw at the same time did not make a sound.
content.summary: Pair of rows of multicolored lights, perfectly stationary.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog around 10:25pm,i live on a hill in la mesa, so i looked back west towards mission valley area and the city lights lit up the sky (was clear out) and i spotted a dark dot because of the lights. as i followed the dot, wings became more visible, because the object had no lights i knew right away this was a "in the moment" don't look away and stay focused. as the object flew over me where there are really no city lights, it had no sound, no lights, it's wings were at 75 degree angle large in size with no type of fuselage visible. if it was a drone, it is unlike any i have ever seen or could find on the internet, it's wings were shaped like a bat or dragon, but yet looked very manufactured or built, not organic in anyway.  i feel the conditions were just right to see it, was like one of those 3d posters from the 80's, once you focus you can see the picture in the poster. i feel this thing has cloaking type of capabilities because of the design, once it is in the dark part of night sky, you can not see it. still overwhelming none the less, would love to have any locals confirm with sighting of there own.
content.summary: Just was looking above to the west for 5sec. it was a fluke i saw it, cloaking type tech. once focused could track, very brief but awsome.
